==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mutoscope
<hw>Mu"to*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mutare</ets> to change + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>A simple
form of moving-picture machine in which the series of views, exhibiting
the successive phases of a scene, are printed on paper and mounted
around the periphery of a wheel. The rotation of the wheel brings them
rapidly into sight, one after another, and the blended effect gives a
semblance of motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mutt</ent>⟦br⟧
